			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	This position is designed for recent graduates who are extremely hungry and passionate about tech startups, but do not have a technical background. The opportunity: work directly with Art.sy&rsquo;s CEO and wear many hats during our most exciting period of growth.</p>
<p>
	Things will evolve, but you can generally expect to spend your time in the following way:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Take on day-to-day tasks from the CEO, such as scheduling meetings/calls, drafting emails, conducting research, running errands.</li>
	<li>
		Help manage our recruiting efforts, search for candidates, screen resumes, track leads.</li>
	<li>
		Assist the CEO in project managing the new Art.sy re-design.</li>
	<li>
		General operations and office management tasks.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	This person is a hustler. They must be extremely organized, have excellent writing skills, and possess a can-do attitude no matter what is assigned to them. They are passionate about the tech world. They want to start up their own company one day.</p>
<p>
	The internship is three months, part-time unpaid, full-time paid, with the potential for full-time employment at completion.</p>
]]></description>
